@tatamotorscars  Hi,
I’m honestly very frustrated with the way this issue is being handled. As discussed earlier with the representative from Durga Motors, Pilerne (Goa), I was clearly assured that the required part for my Tata Punch would arrive by Monday. But I haven’t received a single call or update. It’s been over a month, and my car is still not repaired. The shock absorber issue continues, and the noise makes it impossible to even drive the car. This kind of delay and zero follow-up from such a big company like Tata Motors is unacceptable.
Because of this, I’ve faced huge inconvenience and financial losses. Who is going to take responsibility for all this? If warranty repairs take this long, what’s the point of having one? I would’ve rather paid and got it done long back. This has gone on long enough. I expect a proper update and a resolution immediately.

@tatamotorscars As a middle-class family member, buying a car was always a dream for me. I worked hard and finally purchased a Tata Nexon in January 2025, 

mainly because I deeply respect Sir Ratan Tata for what he has done for the people of India, especially during the COVID pandemic.

I chose Tata Motors because I believed in the safety and values that the brand represents. But within just 7–8 months, my experience has been nothing but frustration and fear

