@tatamotorscars I purchased a Tata Tiago NRG on 24th March 2025 and have driven approximately 3,000 km since then. After 45 days of usage, I encountered an issue related to the exhaust system. I visited the workshop on 15th May 2025 to have it inspected.
Initially, the service personnel informed me that the exhaust component would be replaced. However, upon mentioning that the vehicle is still under warranty, they began denying the existence of any issue, despite the problem being clearly evident. They claimed that the exhaust air was simply hitting the bumper and insisted this was not a defect.
After prolonged discussion and multiple arguments, they finally agreed to replace the part under warranty and informed me that it would take five days as the spare part was not in stock. It has now been over eight days, and I have yet to receive any update or communication from Tata Motors.

