@supriya_thalman : Safety is always a priority for us—we value our lives too and there’s a reason this setup was made. Recently, we traveled from Bangalore to Meghalaya with just two people, so there was no need for a bed. However, this setup was created specifically for our pet, as sitting for long durations hurt her legs.

Also, let’s not forget sleeper buses where people sleep without seat belts for long journeys, or cars with 4 people crammed in the back seat of a 5-seater, often with no one wearing a seat belt. Even in a properly seated 5-seater car, it’s common in India for passengers not to wear belts at the back seat. That said, we’re not endorsing or promoting this as the right way to travel. 

Anyway it’s entirely a personal choice how, where, and when people choose to travel
